# 📚 Book Management API

A simple **Book Management API** built with **Node.js, Express, TypeScript**, and structured using **MVC architecture**.  
This project provides RESTful APIs for managing books with clean code separation and TypeScript support.

---

## 🚀 Features
- Built with **TypeScript** for type safety and maintainability.  
- **MVC architecture** for clean code structure.  
- CRUD operations for managing books.  
- Centralized error handling and validation.  
- Environment variable configuration with `.env`.  
- Postman collection available for testing APIs.  

---

## ⚙️ Tech Stack
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express.js, TypeScript  
- **Database**: MongoDB (Mongoose)  
- **Architecture**: MVC (Model-View-Controller)  

---

## 📂 Project Structure
├── src
│ ├── config # Database and environment configuration
│ ├── constants # App-wide constants (messages, status codes)
│ ├── controllers # Handle request/response
│ ├── middlewares # Middlewares (error handling, auth, etc.)
│ ├── models # MongoDB models (Book schema ,user scheema)
│ ├── routes # API routes (BookRoutes ,UserRoutes , AuthRoutes)
│ ├── validators # express validator request validation
│ ├── logs # API logs (morgan)
│ ├── utils # Helper functions
│ ├── app.ts # all configuration files functions
│ └── index.ts # Entry point
├── .env # Environment variables
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
└── README.md



## 🔑 Environment Variables
Create a `.env` file in the root directory and add the following:

PORT ="7000"
CLIENT_URL="http://localhost:5173"
MONGODB_URL="mongodb+srv://adil:Adil%40953947@cluster0.lfvmsb8.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=Cluster0"
REFRESH_TOKEN_SECRET="Adil@123"
ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET="Adil@123"

LOG_INTERVAL="7d"
NODE_ENV="production"



# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/aadil-nv/Book-Management.git

# Move into the project folder
cd Book-Management

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Run in development mode
npm run dev

# Build for production
npm run build

# Start production server
npm start



